Reasoning: The paper deals with implementing atomic memory objects in distributed storage systems using erasure codes. This topic falls under the broad category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of erasure codes also involves information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses fault-tolerance and error handling, which are relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and cryptography (cs.CR).
